Deployed Ubuntu Server 22.04 with Splunk Enterprise
VM Specs

OS : Ubuntu Server 22.04.5 LTS (Jammy Jellyfish)
RAM : 8 GB
CPU : 2 vCPUs
Disk : 150 GB
Network : Internal Network (labnet)

IP Configuration

Assigned via pfSense DHCP
Subnet : 192.168.10.0/24
Gateway : 192.168.10.254 (pfSense)

Steps

Downloaded Ubuntu Server 22.04 ISO from ubuntu.com
Created VM in VirtualBox with above specs
Completed Ubuntu installation, skipped all optional snaps
Connected to Ubuntu via SSH from Windows host :

bashssh emmanuel@192.168.10.xxx

Downloaded Splunk Enterprise .deb package via SSH session
Installed Splunk :

bashsudo dpkg -i /home/emmanuel/splunk*.deb

Started Splunk and accepted license :

bashsudo /opt/splunk/bin/splunk start --accept-license --run-as-root

Enabled auto-start on boot :

bashsudo /opt/splunk/bin/splunk enable boot-start --run-as-root

Opened required firewall ports :

bashsudo ufw allow 8000/tcp
sudo ufw allow 9997/tcp

Confirmed Splunk web interface accessible from Windows 11 at http://192.168.10.xxx:8000

Troubleshooting

Copy/paste not working : enabled bidirectional clipboard in VirtualBox settings. Used SSH connection as workaround for terminal copy/paste.
Splunk start failed : running Splunk as root requires additional flag. Fixed by adding --run-as-root to start command.

